Numac Oil and Gas Ltd said it expectssignificant improvement in operating performance during 1987.    The company today reported 1986 earnings from continuingoperations of 5,255,179 dlrs, down from 17.6 mln dlrs a yuearearlier, due to lower prices for crude oil and pipelinecapacity constraints.    Numac said changes introduced by federal and provincialgovernments during 1986 should help results. Reuter&#3;